# Salesforce Org Safety

**NEVER** connect to, query, deploy to, or retrieve from any Salesforce org that is not on the `mavenclinic.com` domain.

## Allowed Orgs

| Alias | Username |
|---|---|
| `devjtang` | `jonathan.tang@mavenclinic.com.devjtang1` |
| `mavenprod` | `jonathan.tang@mavenclinic.com` |
| `qa` | `jonathan.tang@mavenclinic.com.qa` |
| `staging` | `jonathan.tang@mavenclinic.com.staging` |

Any other org not listed above is also blocked by default.

## Before Any SF CLI Command

1. Confirm the target org alias or username belongs to `mavenclinic.com`
2. If the alias is unfamiliar, run `sf org list` to verify the domain
3. If in doubt, **stop and ask the user** — do not guess
